data.title: About: WFAX
data.meta_description: WFAX (1220 AM) is a Regional Mexican and Reggaeton formatted broadcast radio station licensed to Falls Church, Virginia, serving Metro Washington, D.C. WFAX is owned and operated by Jose Villafañe's Costa Media, through licensee Costa Media Boston LLC. On June 8, 2022, WFAX had announced that it would change its format from religious talk to Regional Mexican/Spanish Rhythmic branded as "La Pantera" on July 1.
data.text:
dbo:abstract

WFAX (1220 AM) is a Regional Mexican and Reggaeton formatted broadcast radio station licensed to Falls Church, Virginia, serving Metro Washington, D.C. WFAX is owned and operated by Jose Villafañe's Costa Media, through licensee Costa Media Boston LLC. On June 8, 2022, WFAX had announced that it would change its format from religious talk to Regional Mexican/Spanish Rhythmic branded as "La Pantera" on July 1. (en)
